Vehicles that are larger or heavier are generally more speaalized in the kinds of commodities they can transport efficiently.
Inefficiencies may result when such vehicles are used for carrying other commodities on a backhm.d.
Access restrictions reduce the number of shippers that can be served by longer or heavier vehicles, limiting both the markets that can be served by such vehicles and the opportunities for obtaining backhauls.
